# Faith Generation App — Core Development Rules

## Project Identity

Faith Generation is a Christian mobile Bible school app. Content (modules, lessons, podcasts, sermons) is free and fetched from Storyblok CMS. User auth and progress live in Supabase. Videos are hosted on Vimeo. The UI language defaults to Dutch; English is the fallback locale.

## Tech Stack (exact versions from package.json)

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| Framework | React Native 0.81.5 + Expo SDK 54 |
| Router | Expo Router 6 (file-based, `expo-router/drawer` for main nav) |
| Styling | NativeWind v4 + Tailwind CSS 3 |
| UI primitives | Gluestack UI (`@gluestack-ui/core`) |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 strict mode |
| State | React Context + TanStack Query v5 |
| Backend | Supabase JS v2 |
| CMS | Storyblok (`storyblok` package) |
| Video | `expo-video` (never `expo-av` — deprecated in SDK 54) |
| Fonts | Poppins 400/500/600/700 via `@expo-google-fonts/poppins` |
| Animation | `@legendapp/motion`, `react-native-reanimated` v4 |
| Keyboard | `react-native-keyboard-controller` (KeyboardProvider wraps the whole app) |
| Forms | `FormScrollView` from `@/components/ui/FormScrollView` |
| Formatting | Prettier |

## Provider Tree (app/_layout.tsx)

The exact nesting order — never rearrange:

```
GestureHandlerRootView
  └─ KeyboardProvider
       └─ TypographyProvider       (contexts/TypographyContext)
            └─ QueryProvider       (providers/QueryProvider)
                 └─ AuthProvider   (contexts/AuthContext)
                      └─ ThemeProvider   (contexts/ThemeContext)
                           └─ LanguageProvider (contexts/LanguageContext)
                                └─ ToastProvider (contexts/ToastContext)
                                     └─ ThemeLayout (components/ThemeLayout)
```

## Navigation Architecture

**Root:** `app/_layout.tsx` → `ThemeLayout` → Stack with `index`, `(auth)`, `(main)`

**Auth group** (`app/(auth)/`): Unauthenticated only — login and register.

**Main group** (`app/(main)/`): Drawer navigation (right-side). Requires session. Uses `SectionNavigationContext` to show a loading overlay during drawer transitions.

Drawer screens (exact names from `_layout.tsx`):
- `index` — "Jouw Overzicht" (home/overview)
- `bibleschool` — Bible school with its own tabs inside
- `admin` — Admin panel (admin users only)
- `podcasts`
- `sermons`
- `faith-business-school`
- `profile`
- `badges`
- `settings`

**Bibleschool sub-navigation:** `app/(main)/bibleschool/` uses a `(tabs)/` route group containing:
- `(tabs)/index` — bibleschool home/overview
- `(tabs)/modules/` — module list
- `(tabs)/modules/[id]/` — module detail (with its own `_layout.tsx`)
- `(tabs)/modules/[id]/[lessonId]` — lesson detail (video + handout)
- `(tabs)/modules/[id]/exam` — module quiz

**Always navigate using `constants/routes.ts`:**

```typescript
import { routes } from '@/constants/routes';
router.push(routes.bibleschool());
router.push(routes.bibleschoolModuleLesson(moduleId, lessonId));
router.push(routes.settings('preferences'));
```

Never hardcode route strings like `'/(main)/bibleschool'`.

## Internationalization

**5 supported languages:**

| Code | Name | Flag | Shown in UI? |
|---|---|---|---|
| `en` | English | 🇬🇧 | No (fallback only) |
| `nl` | Dutch | 🇳🇱 | Yes |
| `bg` | Bulgarian | 🇧🇬 | Yes |
| `hi` | Hindi | 🇮🇳 | Yes |
| `id` | Indonesian | 🇮🇩 | Yes |

**Important:** English is the fallback locale but is hidden from the language switcher UI (`LANGUAGES_FOR_UI` filters it out). When adding new UI strings, add translations to **all 5 locale files**: `en.json`, `nl.json`, `bg.json`, `hi.json`, `id.json`.

**Usage:**
```typescript
const { t } = useTranslation(); // from @/hooks/useTranslation
t('auth.login')
t('common.loading')
```

**Rules:**
- Never hardcode Dutch or English strings in components
- All user-facing text uses `t()` — labels, buttons, placeholders, error messages
- Language preference stored in `user_settings` (key: `language`) when logged in, in AsyncStorage when not

## TypeScript Standards

- Strict mode — no `any` unless genuinely unavoidable
- `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections/utility types
- **`undefined` not `null` for optional values** — optional TS properties are `T | undefined`
- No unused variables, imports, or arguments
- Explicit return types on service methods; inferred types fine for local variables

## Component Architecture

- Functional components with hooks only
- Max ~250 lines per component; extract into sub-components if larger
- Named exports from `_components/` files; default exports for page/screen components
- No inline styles when a NativeWind class exists
- `SafeAreaView` always from `react-native-safe-area-context`, never from `react-native`

