## Services & Data Layer

### BaseService Pattern

Every domain service extends `BaseService` from `@/services/api/baseService.ts`:

```typescript
import { BaseService } from '@/services/api/baseService';

export class MyService extends BaseService {
  protected tableName = 'my_table';

  async getByUser(userId: string) {
    return this.list<MyType>({
      filters: [{ field: 'user_id', operator: 'eq', value: userId }],
      sort: [{ field: 'created_at', ascending: false }],
    });
  }
}

export const myService = new MyService();
```

**BaseService public/protected methods:**
- `get<T>(id, options?)` — fetch single record by id
- `list<T>(options?)` — fetch array with filters/sort/pagination
- `listPaginated<T>(options?)` — returns `PaginatedResponse<T>`
- `create<T, D>(data)` — insert, returns created record
- `createWithUser<T, D>(data)` — injects `user_id` automatically
- `update<T, D>(id, data)` — update by id
- `upsertWithConflict<T, D>(data, { onConflict })` — upsert
- `delete(id)` — delete by id
- `batchCreate<T, D>(items[])` — multi-insert
- `batchDelete(ids[])` — multi-delete
- `count(filters?)` — count records
- `exists(id)` — boolean existence check
- `executeRpc<T>(name, params?)` — call a Postgres RPC
- `getCurrentUserId()` — gets auth user id (throws if unauthenticated)
- `injectUserId(data)` — adds `user_id` field to data

