### TanStack Query

Always use TanStack Query for server state. Never `useEffect` + `useState` for data fetching.

```typescript
// Queries
const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: queryKeys.progress.lesson(userId, lessonId),
  queryFn: () => lessonProgressService.getByUserLesson(userId, lessonId),
  staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000,
});

// Mutations
const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (input) => lessonProgressService.upsertProgress(input),
  onSuccess: () => {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: queryKeys.progress.lesson(userId, lessonId) });
    toast.success(t('common.saved'));
  },
  onError: (err) => toast.error(err.message),
});
```

**Query key factory** is at `services/queryKeys.ts`. Always use it. Never write raw arrays for query keys.

## Error Handling

Services throw `AppError` (from `@/services/api/baseService.ts`):

```typescript
import { AppError, AppErrorCode } from '@/services/api/baseService';

try {
  await authService.login(data);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof AppError) {
    switch (err.code) {
      case AppErrorCode.AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS:
        setError(t('auth.invalidCredentials'));
        break;
      case AppErrorCode.AUTH_USER_EXISTS:
        setError(t('auth.userExists'));
        break;
      default:
        toast.error(err.message);
    }
  }
}
```

Error codes: `UNKNOWN`, `NETWORK`, `AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS`, `AUTH_USER_EXISTS`, `AUTH_WEAK_PASSWORD`, `AUTH_SESSION_MISSING`, `DATABASE_CONFLICT`, `DATABASE_NOT_FOUND`, `DATABASE_VALIDATION`, `PERMISSION_DENIED`, `RATE_LIMIT`.

## UI Patterns

### Theme

Always use `useTheme()` from `@/hooks/useTheme`. Never hardcode colors.

```typescript
const theme = useTheme();
// theme.pageBg, theme.cardBg, theme.cardBorder
// theme.textPrimary, theme.textSecondary, theme.textTertiary
// theme.buttonPrimary, theme.buttonPrimaryContrast
// theme.buttonDecline, theme.buttonAccept
// theme.isDark (boolean)
```

Full token reference in `.cursor/rules/modern-design-2026.mdc`.

### Loading States

Full-screen loading → `LoadingScreen` from `@/components/ui/LoadingScreen`. Never bare `ActivityIndicator`.

```typescript
import { LoadingScreen } from '@/components/ui/LoadingScreen';
if (isLoading) return <LoadingScreen message={t('common.loading')} />;
```

### Toast Notifications

```typescript
import { useToast } from '@/hooks/useToast';
const toast = useToast();
toast.success(t('common.saved'));
toast.error(t('common.error'));
```

### Forms

Use `FormScrollView` from `@/components/ui/FormScrollView` (KeyboardAwareScrollView). Chain inputs with refs:

```typescript
const emailRef = useRef<TextInput>(null);
const passwordRef = useRef<TextInput>(null);

<FormScrollView>
  <InputField ref={emailRef} returnKeyType="next" blurOnSubmit={false}
    onSubmitEditing={() => passwordRef.current?.focus()} />
  <InputField ref={passwordRef} returnKeyType="done" />
</FormScrollView>
```

Never use `KeyboardAvoidingView` + `ScrollView`. Never use `KeyboardToolbar`.

### Lists

Use `FlatList` or `FlashList` for lists. Never `.map()` inside `ScrollView` for long lists.

## Supabase Database Schema

Tables in `public`:

| Table | Key columns |
|---|---|
| `profiles` | `id` (FK auth.users), `full_name`, `avatar_url` |
| `user_lesson_progress` | `user_id`, `lesson_id`, `module_id`, `completed` (bool), `video_position_seconds`, `completed_at` |
| `user_module_progress` | `user_id`, `module_id`, `status` (`locked\|in_progress\|completed`), `progress_percentage`, `completed_at` |
| `user_quiz_attempts` | `user_id`, `module_id`, `attempt_number`, `score_percentage`, `passed`, `answers` (jsonb), `correct_count`, `total_count` |
| `user_settings` | `user_id`, `key`, `value` (jsonb) — key-value store |
| `badges` | `id`, `key`, `title`, `description`, `icon_url` |
| `user_badges` | `user_id`, `badge_id`, `earned_at` |
| `user_streaks` | `user_id`, `current_streak`, `longest_streak`, `last_activity_date` |
| `user_notifications` | `user_id`, `title`, `body`, `type`, `read`, `created_at` |

RLS: all tables enforce `auth.uid() = user_id`.

RPCs: `get_user_setting(p_user_id, p_key)`, `set_user_setting(p_user_id, p_key, p_value)`, analytics RPCs for admin.

**Migration naming:** `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`. Always run `date -u +%Y%m%d%H%M%S` before naming.

## Storyblok Content Structure

Content types used:
- `bibleschool_category` — module container (fetched by locale)
- Module stories contain: `title`, `description`, `vimeo_id`, lesson references
- Lesson stories contain: `title`, `vimeo_id`, `content` (rich text), handout data

Fetch with `EXPO_PUBLIC_STORYBLOK_ACCESS_TOKEN`. See `services/storyblok/client.ts` and `hooks/useBibleschoolContent.ts`.

